So you've bought a Tesla — congratulations. Now you need a home charger. And here's the good news: every Tesla sold in the UK uses a **Type 2 connector**, which means you're not locked into buying Tesla's own charger. You've got options.

But which charger is actually best for a Tesla owner? The Tesla Wall Connector has the obvious brand appeal, but third-party chargers like the Ohme Home Pro and Myenergi Zappi offer features Tesla's own hardware simply can't match — particularly around smart tariff integration and energy management.

We've compared the top five options head-to-head so you can make the right call.

