## Do You Need a Tesla-Branded Charger?

Short answer: **no**. Every Tesla currently sold in the UK — Model 3, Model Y, Model S, and Model X — uses the standard **Type 2 (Mennekes) connector**. This is the same connector used by virtually every other EV sold in Europe.

That means any home charger with a Type 2 tethered cable (or an untethered socket) will work perfectly with your Tesla. You won't lose any charging speed, and your car will charge at the full 7.4kW that a standard UK single-phase supply allows.

The only thing you *might* miss is native Tesla app integration — but as we'll explain, the third-party apps are often better anyway.

