## Frequently Asked Questions

### Can I use any EV charger with a Tesla in the UK?

Yes. All Tesla models sold in the UK use the standard **Type 2 connector**, which is the same as virtually every other EV on the European market. Any home charger with a Type 2 tethered cable or untethered socket will work with your Tesla at full speed.

### Is the Tesla Wall Connector worth it?

It depends on your priorities. If you value seamless Tesla app integration and have three-phase power, it's a solid choice. But for most UK Tesla owners on single-phase power, a third-party charger like the Ohme Home Pro offers better smart features, OZEV grant eligibility, and significant energy cost savings.

### Does Intelligent Octopus Go work with all chargers?

Intelligent Octopus Go works at the **car level** with compatible vehicles (including all current Tesla models). However, certain chargers like the **Ohme Home Pro** also integrate at the charger level, giving you better data and more control. The Tesla Wall Connector does not have charger-level integration with the tariff.

### How fast will a home charger charge my Tesla?

On a standard UK single-phase supply, a 7.4kW charger will add roughly **25–30 miles of range per hour**. A Tesla Model 3 Long Range (with a ~75kWh battery) would go from near-empty to full in about 10–11 hours — easily done overnight. For most daily use, you'll only need to top up 30–50% each night, which takes 4–6 hours.

### Can I get the OZEV grant for a Tesla charger?

You can claim the OZEV grant (up to £350) for any approved charger installed by an OZEV-registered installer. The **Ohme Home Pro, Myenergi Zappi, Easee One, and Hypervolt** all qualify. The Tesla Wall Connector is generally not eligible through standard installation routes, as Tesla doesn't operate an OZEV-registered installation network in the UK.

